IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE EDUCATION, INFORMATION, AND SERVICES RELATED TO WOMEN'S AND MEN'S HEALTH.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION'S MISSION IS TO IMPROVE INDIVIDUAL AND COMMUNITY WELLNESS IN THE COASTAL BEND BY PROVIDING CLINICAL AND EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS TO PREVENT CHRONIC DISEASES, UNPLANNED PREGNANCY, SEXUALLY TRANSMITTED INFECTIONS INCLUDING HIV, AND DOMESTIC VIOLENCE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ROBIN KENNEDY, TREASURER, IS RELATED TO FELLOW BOARD MEMBER, SHANNON MAYO, AND JAN BARTLETT IS MARRIED TO FELLOW BOARD MEMBER, DAVID BARTLETT. SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE POLICY IS MONITORED AND ENFORCED THROUGH OVERSIGHT OF CONTRACTING, PURCHASING, AND HIRING DECISIONS AND THROUGH A REVIEW OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ADMINISTRATIVE POLICIES BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ON A REGULAR BASIS. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND FINANCE DIRECTOR ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR OVERSIGHT OF ALL CONTRACTS, PURCHASES, OR HIRES THAT MIGHT INVOLVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST. THE BOARD IS INFORMED OF ANY SIGNIFICANT CHANGES IN CONTRACTS, PURCHASES, OR HIRES SO THEY MAY ALSO PROVIDE OVERSIGHT ON THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. STAFF RECEIVES AN ORIENTATION ON ADMINISTRATIVE POLICIES, INCLUDING CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES, AT THE TIME OF HIRE SO THEY ALSO ARE AWARE AND CAN REPORT ANY PERCEIVED CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECEIVES COMPARABILITY DATA AND SETS THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY AND IT IS DOCUMENTED IN BOARD MEETING MINUTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.

THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS MAINTAINS RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSEEING THE AUDIT, APPROVING ISSUANCE OF THE AUDIT REPORT, AND FOR SELECTION OF INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANTS TO AUDIT THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THERE HAS BEEN NO CHANGE IN THIS PROCESS FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
